observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct:

a. The Inventory Committee to prepare a systematic and well-planned physical inventory taking and prepare the corresponding Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE) and ensure that all the necessary data are provided thereon;

b. The Municipal Treasurer to ensure that all PPEs owned by the municipality are duly recorded in the Property Cards (PCs) maintained by the Property Unit and properties issued to end-users are provided with PAR; and property stickers;

c. The Municipal Accountant to maintain, and update the PPE Ledger Cards.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the Municipal Accountant to:

a. cause the remittance of the balances to the GSIS, Pag-IBIG and PhilHealth to avoid incurrence of penalties and surcharges, then remit accordingly;

b. Maintain subsidiary ledgers and exert effort to reconcile the amounts and balances of Inter-Agency Payables accounts.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the Human Resource and Management Officer the following courses of action:

1. Assess its existing Organizational Structure so that the ideal number of plantilla personnel will be established and submit a report with recommendations thereon to the LCE for approval by the appropriate bodies;

2. Create policies and guidelines to address the issue on the necessity and propriety of hiring JOs taking into consideration the existing regular employees;

3. Limit the hiring of personnel under Job Order contracts to those extremely necessary and deploy only to offices that are actually in need of their services;

4. Submit primary personal identification, undergo interview and evaluate the performance of each to give assurance that the risk identified above are addressed; and,

5. Incorporate in the contract the necessary details such as the job description/specific work to be done and the hours to be rendered, the certification as to the necessity of hiring the Job Order, certification as to the existence of the appropriation, and that the person duly signified the intent which was considered by the hiring agency.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the Municipal Accountant to:

a. Reconcile the total of the balances in the subsidiary ledgers with the balance in the General Ledger by exerting efforts to identify the transactions which caused the difference of P9,677,874.51;

b. Exert effort to ascertain the errors which brought the attention on the negative balance of Due to NGAs, and cause the immediate adjustment and correction of the same; and

c. Ascertain the programs, projects, and activities of the fund transfers through the Memorandum Agreement (MOA) and/or any communication received from source agency;

We recommended for the Municipal Mayor to:

a)	Ensure compliance with the terms of agreement provided in the signed MOA of all funds transferred;

b)	Instruct the Municipal Treasurer to submit the liquidation report of the fund transferred intended for the grant of One COVID-19 Allowance (OCA) to DOH so that subsequent fund transfer may be made;

c)	Direct the Municipal Accountant to submit the lacking disbursement vouchers and the required supporting documents on all payments to contractor; and to discontinue the practice of separating the DVs and its supporting documents from the monthly submission of accounts.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor to direct the Human Resource and Management Officer the following courses of action:

1.	Assess its existing Organizational Structure so that the ideal number of plantilla personnel will be established and submit a report with recommendations thereon to the LCE for approval by the appropriate bodies;

2.	Create policies and guidelines to address the issue on the necessity and propriety of hiring JOs taking into consideration the existing regular employees;

3.	Limit the hiring of personnel under Job Order contracts to those extremely necessary and deploy only to offices that are actually in need of their services; 

4.	Submit primary personal identification, undergo interview and evaluate the performance of each to give assurance that the risk identified above are addressed; and,

5.	Incorporate in the contract the necessary details such as the job description/specific work to be done and the hours to be rendered, the certification as to the necessity of hiring the Job Order, certification as to the existence of the appropriation, and that the person duly signified the intent which was considered by the hiring agency.

