We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:

a.    Constitute an Inventory Committee that will conduct the physical count of the local road networks of the municipality and prepare and submit the RPCLRN not later than January 31 of each year; 

b.    Require the GSO to prepare at the end of each accounting period a Report on Local Road Network;

c.    Require the Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and the GSO with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects; and 

d.    Require the Municipal Accountant to provide the required disclosure in the Notes to FS as required by COA Circular No. 2015-008.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the Municipal Accountant to:

a.    Reconcile the total of the balances in the subsidiary ledgers with the balance in the General Ledger by exerting efforts to identify the transactions which caused the difference of P9,677,874.51;

b.    Exert effort to ascertain the errors which brought the negative balance of Due to NGAs, and cause the immediate correction of the same;

c.    Ascertain the programs, projects and activities of the fund transfers through the Memorandum of Agreement (MOA) and/or any communication received from source agency; and

d.    Prepare and submit the Fund Utilization Report for each fund transfer, to identify unused or excesses of funds in the hands of the municipality and cause the immediate return of these funds.

