We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:

Require the officers and employees concerned to liquidate their cash advances within the prescribed period;

Instruct the Municipal Accountant to strengthen internal control measures over cash advances to ensure timely submission of liquidation documents and full accounting of accountabilities of accountable officers;

Direct the Municipal Accountant to refrain from granting cash advances to employees if previous cash advance is not yet settled; and

Require the Municipal Accountant to issue demand letters to the accountable officers to settle their unliquidated cash advances and refund all unexpended balances, if any.

